p On a good day, you wake up easily: willing and able to start the day. When you are depressed, however, you find it difficult to wake up without stimulants. Even people who are not bipolar may have difficulty starting the day without caffeine.
p The BipolarType theory asserts that although you can be more or less depressed on different days (Bipolar) the form of your depression remains the same (Type).
